The U.S. increased its use of
renewable energy other than nuclear and hydroelectric by more
than  China  last year,  BP Plc (BP/)  said.  U.S. consumption rose by 6.4 million tons of oil equivalent
while use in China jumped by 5.8 million tons, according to the
BP Statistical Review of World Energy 2012 report.  Chinaâ€™s use of renewables, which increased from a lower
base, jumped 48 percent to 17.7 million tons compared with 2010.
